@MK-61 I figured it out. I actually had found the solution yesterday but had a stupid error in it, that I couldn't see until now. Thank you very much for your help. Don't worry about being a bad teacher, you helped me a lot without giving too much away. Here's my solution:
```
function steamrollArray(arr) {
  // I'm a steamroller, baby

  var finalArr = [];

  for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (Array.isArray(arr[i])) {
      finalArr = finalArr.concat(steamrollArray(arr[i]));
    } else {
      finalArr.push(arr[i]);
    }      
  }    
  return finalArr;
}

steamrollArray([[["a"]], [["b"]]]);
```

